    diagnostics: ["Perform Braden Scale assessment on admission, every shift (acute care), and with ANY change in condition", "Conduct comprehensive skin assessment on admission and every shift — inspect ALL bony prominences: sacrum, coccyx, heels, ischial tuberosities, greater trochanters, scapulae, occiput, ears", "Assess for Stage 1 pressure injury: non-blanchable erythema of intact skin (press firmly with finger — if redness does NOT blanch, capillary damage has occurred)", "Evaluate nutritional status: serum albumin, prealbumin, caloric and protein intake, weight trends", "Assess continence status and current moisture management plan", "Review medical devices for proper fit and skin condition beneath/around devices", "Evaluate support surface appropriateness for patient's risk level"],
