      question: "A patient on cholestyramine for PBC-related pruritus asks when to take her thyroid medication. What is the correct guidance?",
      options: ["At the same time as cholestyramine", "Take thyroid medication at least 1 hour BEFORE or 4-6 hours AFTER cholestyramine — cholestyramine binds drugs in the GI tract and prevents their absorption", "Timing doesn't matter", "Stop the thyroid medication while on cholestyramine"],
      correct: 1,
